channel.title: Most memorable line you've ever heard.
channel.description:
Just as the title suggests this is the place to post what you think are hilarious (Wether or not they were intended to be funny) or just plain baddass lines. It doesn't particularity matter were you heard/read it (film/tv/book/your best mate, you name it) and sourcing it is preferred were possible so that A) So that we know what your on about B) so that we can enjoy it in context.
p.s. I know that no-one will listen if I say constructive comments only so please, one reply for each post; each; people
p.s.s. Try to avoid the obvious ones, I think everyone on this forum has heard "I'll be back" at least once.
So starting us off are the lines
"Sir, I'm going to have to ask you to leave the Donut" From Iron man 2.
and
"yeah, I sure hope he doesn't see us in this bright yellow banana pentol" "Are you trying to say your embarrassed to be seen in an American classic?" From, well a prize for who guesses where its from.
